title: Police rubbish claims of road closures due to Jong-un arrival
text:
KUALA LUMPUR: Police have rubbished a voice note going viral on WhatsApp, claiming that major roads and highways in the Klang Valley were closed to make way for the arrival of North Korean leader Kim Jong-un.    
The minute-long voice note alleged that traffic was backed up past the Bukit Jalil exit due to closures along the Sungai Besi toll plaza heading to Kuala Lumpur.  
It also claimed that the stretch of road from Seri Kembangan to Kuchai Lama on the Maju Expressway (MEX) was closed, causing chaos in Seri Kembangan and Seri Serdang.  
Kim was supposedly on his way to Hospital Kuala Lumpur.  
When contacted Monday, City traffic chief Asst Comm Mohd Nadzri Hussain confirmed that the information in the voice note was fake and urged the public to not disseminate false information.   
“It’s not true. Don’t believe it and please don’t share fake information,” he said.    
Kim Jong-nam, the half-brother of Jong-un, was killed after two women wiped his face with the banned VX nerve agent at Kuala Lumpur International Airport 2 on Feb 13. He was waiting to board a flight to Macau.
Malaysia is waiting for the next of kin to identify the body and provide DNA samples for identity confirmation. 
However, Health Minister Datuk Seri Dr S. Subramaniam said there  were other ways should no next-of-kin come forward to claim Jong-nam’s body or provide a DNA sample. 
“These include dental profiling and examining the body for identifying marks," he said on Sunday.
